==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subarration
<hw>Sub`ar*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>sub-</ets> + L. <ets>arra</ets>, <ets>arrha</ets>, earnest money.
See <er>Earnest</er> a pledge.]</ety> <def>The ancient custom of
betrothing by the bestowal, on the part of the man, of marriage gifts or
tokens, as money, rings, or other presents, upon the woman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

